  "text": "Correlations between observations are a recognised statistical problem in many areas of medical research, [CITATION_1] including ophthalmology. [CITATION_2] If such correlations are not taken into account in statistical analyses, there may be errors in the results obtained, usually resulting in falsely precise confidence intervals and falsely small p values.",
